{"data":{"featured":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"OpenClimateFix Data Pipeline","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/be5ed/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/8bb35/cover.jpg 125w,\n/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/f505e/cover.jpg 250w,\n/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/be5ed/cover.jpg 500w","sizes":"(min-width: 500px) 500px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/3ebc4/cover.avif 125w,\n/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/a9ff4/cover.avif 250w,\n/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/a61b1/cover.avif 500w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 500px) 500px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/d66e1/cover.webp 125w,\n/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/e7160/cover.webp 250w,\n/static/26b2068fa7371c8b81a6462ebe66c73e/5f169/cover.webp 500w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 500px) 500px, 100vw"}]},"width":700,"height":700}}},"tech":["Python","Apache Airflow","PyTorch","Graph Neural Networks","Apache Kafka"],"github":"https://github.com/openclimatefix","external":"https://github.com/openclimatefix","cta":"https://github.com/openclimatefix"},"html":"<p>Contributed to OpenClimateFix's open-source weather forecasting data pipeline, focusing on refining data processing workflows and implementing anomaly detection in graph neural network (GNN) weather models. The pipeline processes terabytes of meteorological data from multiple sources including satellite imagery, weather stations, and radar systems to produce high-resolution forecasts.</p>\n<p>Key contributions include building robust data validation and quality assurance pipelines using Apache Airflow, implementing anomaly detection algorithms to flag suspicious weather data points, and optimizing the GNN model training pipeline for distributed training across GPU clusters. The work aims to improve the accuracy and reliability of AI-driven weather forecasting, which is critical for renewable energy grid management and climate change mitigation efforts.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"3D Web Interactivity with Three.js","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/d2194/cover.png","srcSet":"/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/cebcc/cover.png 175w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/272cf/cover.png 350w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/d2194/cover.png 700w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/b50c4/cover.png 1400w","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/9aa63/cover.avif 175w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/e6db6/cover.avif 350w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/f47db/cover.avif 700w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/8fee6/cover.avif 1400w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/240e7/cover.webp 175w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/faefe/cover.webp 350w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/d5dc4/cover.webp 700w,\n/static/df37355329a987bce0ee7b9297c3fbac/e2f1a/cover.webp 1400w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"}]},"width":700,"height":438}}},"tech":["Three.js","WebGL","JavaScript","GLSL Shaders","React"],"github":"https://github.com/glitch401","external":"https://github.com/glitch401","cta":"https://github.com/glitch401"},"html":"<p>Built interactive 3D web experiences using Three.js and WebGL, exploring the intersection of data visualization and immersive web technologies. The project includes real-time 3D data visualizations, particle systems, and custom GLSL shaders for rendering complex scientific datasets in the browser.</p>\n<p>Features include a physics-based particle simulation engine running entirely on the GPU via compute shaders, interactive 3D graph visualizations for network data, and procedural terrain generation using noise functions. The project demonstrates how modern web technologies can be leveraged to create compelling, interactive scientific visualizations that run at 60fps in the browser.</p>"}}]}}}